'''Republic Executive Directive 9302-84121''' was an executive order issued by the [[Office of the Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Office of the Supreme Chancellor]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] on 13:5:23 GrS ([[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]]). The directive authorized government seizure of the [[HoloNet/Legends|HoloNet]] channel that carried [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]], allowing the Republic to re-purpose it as a [[Republic Military/Legends|military]] communications channel. It was issued in response to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] between the Republic and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]], which had erupted days prior with the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|Battle of Geonosis]].

==Description==
Republic Executive Directive 9302-84121 was a decree of the [[Office of the Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Office of the Supreme Chancellor]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. The directive claimed the [[HoloNet/Legends|HoloNet]] channel that regularly featured [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]] for exclusive usage by the [[Republic Military/Legends|newly-formed Republic Military]]. The nationalization of the channel was intended to expire when the state of emergency instigated by the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] was brought to an end.<ref name="HNN REBS" />

==History==
{{Quote|For future updates, set transceiver to Approved Government Channels|Republic Emergency Broadcast System|<ref name="HNN REBS" />}}
In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]], which had plagued the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] for two [[Standard year/Legends|years]], reached a fever pitch and erupted into [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]-wide [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> The conflict inspired the Office of the [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]],<ref name="HNN REBS" /> at the time occupied by [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] of [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]],<ref name="NEC" /> to issue a state of emergency. During this time, the Chancellor's office issued Republic Executive Directive 9302-84121 in order to appropriate control of the HoloNet channel that carried HoloNet News and reserve it for usage by the Republic's Armed Forces.<ref name="HNN REBS" />

From that point onward, citizens who attempted to access the channel were met with a bulletin from the [[Republic Emergency Broadcasting System]], which described the directive and instructed viewers to change their transceivers to a government-approved channel.<ref name="HNN REBS" /> Though HoloNet News was briefly shut down as a result of this order, it returned later in the Clone Wars, albeit in a more limited format.<ref name="HNN Insider">[[HoloNet News (Insider)|''HoloNet News'']] series&mdash;''[[Star Wars Insider]]''</ref><ref name="HNN Podcast">[[HoloNet News (podcast)|HoloNet News podcast]]</ref> Dubbed "Republic HoloNet News" during the conflict, the program made sporadic updates that focused on news from the frontlines of the war<ref name="HNN Insider" /> and aired pro-Republic programs such as ''[[A Galaxy Divided]]'',<ref name="HNN Podcast" /> while eschewing the more trivial "Sports" and "Life" features that had been present in its previous incarnation.<ref name="HNN Insider" />

==Behind the scenes==
Republic Executive Directive 9302-84121 was created as a way to bring an end to [[HoloNet News (original website)|HoloNet News]],<ref name="HNN REBS" /> an online feature created in [[2002]] to generate hype before the release of [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].<ref name="Corroney">{{Blog|joecorroney|22|Mr. Hammond, HoloNet News is back online! (sort of&hellip;)}}</ref> Coinciding with the release of the film, website updates ceased and content on the main page was replaced with a message detailing the suspension of HoloNet News with the issuing of Republic Executive Directive 9302-84121.<ref name="HNN REBS" />

